biv
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a hut, or tent etc. built or used as a temporary shelter; and esp. as bivvy (or biv) freq. among outdoors people for a purpose-built rough shelter or sheltered camping place.
Origin: abbreviation
Register: informal
Register 2:
Domain: Sport
Region: [none]
See: bivouac, bivvy.
Pronunciation:
Notes: Google search Nov 2006: NZ 20 , Austral 0, UK 0 hits.
